place.name: EAST WALTON
place.gazetteerText: WALTON (East), a parish in Freebridge-Lynn district, Norfolk; 1½ mile N of Narborough r. station, and 8 ESE of Lynn. Post town, Lynn. Acres, 2,659. Real property, £1,663. Pop., 175. Houses, 36. The manor belongs to A. Hamond, Esq. The living is a vicarage, united with Gayton-Thorpe, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £424.* Patron, A. Hamond, Esq. The church is later English. There are a national school, and charities £24. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
